Durban - THE driver of a minibus taxi, that allegedly ran a red robot and hit into three teenage girls, is expected to appear at the Ntuzuma Magistrate's Court today. The 33-year-old who handed himself over to KwaMashu Police yesterday afternoon is facing three charges of culpable homicide. On Wednesday morning the girls aged between 13 and 14 were on Dumisani Makhaye Drive on their way to Newlands East Secondary School when the taxi ploughed into them. Three of the girls had sustained critical injuries and died on scene while a fourth, is recovering in hospital. According to The Mercury Newspaper, the taxi “allegedly failed to stop at a red traffic light and ploughed into them”. Family members of the girls could be seen arriving at the accident and crying for their losses. Residents living in the area could also be seen distraught and angered by the actions of the taxi driver. At the time, Department of Education spokesperson Kwazi Mthethwa said the MEC Mthandeni Dlungwane had been “heavily heartbroken” by the news of the accident and would soon be visiting the families of the girls. POST